      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RIBERY (1) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 4.5 lengths at Gawler in a handy 22.68 beating Waratah Who. Nicely placed here on the inside and in form and has the ability. Expected to go well again. CERISE (7) made light work of the tricky draw with a fast early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (17.00) at Murray Bridge Straight over 300m. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Hard to beat again. VICTA HOWARD (4) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (31.57) last time in a Grade 6 at this track. Form at this distance is sound. Has the ability to give this a shake. JUST LIKE FRED (2) cannot be underestimated.",
